# Layer 1 — Host tools & applications (Homebrew).
#
# Managed by chezmoi; rendered to ~/.config/homebrew/Brewfile. This is the
# global Brewfile: `brew bundle --global` resolves here via XDG_CONFIG_HOME
# (set in .zshrc). Installs are driven by the run_onchange brew hook during
# `chezmoi apply`, which re-bundles whenever this file changes.
#
# DESIGN CHOICE: chezmoi's idiom for packages is declarative data in
# .chezmoidata + a run_onchange script that pipes a Brewfile to stdin:
#   https://www.chezmoi.io/user-guide/advanced/install-packages-declaratively/
# We intentionally DON'T use that. Instead the Brewfile DSL is the source of
# truth and we keep it persistent on disk, because:
#   - A real file enables the by-hand maintenance lifecycle the stdin approach
#     can't: `brew bundle check/cleanup/list/edit --global` (cleanup with no
#     file on disk reads "nothing declared" and would uninstall everything).
#   - The DSL natively expresses options a flat data list can't without schema
#     work (mas IDs, `brew args:`, casks, vscode extensions, taps).
# Profile selection is a couple of inline conditionals below — cheaper than the
# data indirection. Revisit deliberately if the idiom evolves or needs grow.
#
# LAYERING RULE: language-ecosystem CLIs that drag a runtime do NOT belong here.
# They live with their package manager — Python tools in uv (setup-stuff/uv),
# Node tools in pnpm. Only standalone binaries (incl. ruff, biome) stay in brew.

# --- Runtime managers (Layer 1 seeds Layer 2) ---
brew "mise"

# --- Shell & core CLI ---
brew "chezmoi"
brew "direnv"
